      <!-- Overview -->
      <div class="content-section">
        <div class="content-label">Overview</div>
        <h2 class="content-h2">What is <em>Viscosupplementation?</em></h2>
        <p class="content-p">
          Healthy joints are filled with synovial fluid — a thick, slippery substance that acts as a lubricant and shock absorber. In osteoarthritis and joint degeneration, this fluid thins out and loses its cushioning properties, resulting in bone-on-bone friction, pain, swelling, and stiffness.
        </p>
        <p class="content-p">
          Viscosupplementation involves injecting <strong>Hyaluronic Acid (HA)</strong> — the same molecule found naturally in joint fluid — directly into the affected joint. This restores viscosity, reduces inflammation, and provides the joint with a natural cushion, allowing you to move freely and without pain.
        </p>
        <p class="content-p">
          Dr. Sarish Sharma uses this procedure as a <strong>first-line treatment</strong> for mild to moderate knee and hip arthritis — delaying or even preventing the need for joint replacement surgery entirely.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Benefits -->
      <div class="content-section">
